<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I wanted to try to make a kind of &quot;Arch based Mint&quot;.</p> <p>One VM and lots of yays later, here it is, my very own March Linux (just kidding about the name, this is just a simple test I did to see how close I could get to Mint, apparently VERY!)</p> <p>I even included the slick greeter so at no point does it look like I&#39;m using Arch.</p> <p>Anyway, it was fun to make and I thought I&#39;d post it here for anyone with some time to burn in a pointless exercise, such as yours truly.</p> <p><a href="https://imgur.com/a/dnv4DiS">https://imgur.com/a/dnv4DiS</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/someuser_2"> /u/someuser_2 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/13jpb2l/march_linux/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/13jpb2l/march_linux/">[comments]</a></span>